genresAdvancedInfo.name: experimental big band
genresAdvancedInfo.description: Experimental big band is a genre that combines the traditional sounds of big band jazz with experimental techniques and instrumentation. It often incorporates unconventional rhythms, harmonies, and textures, and it frequently uses electronic and acoustic instruments in unconventional ways. The genre is characterized by its use of complex arrangements and its willingness to push the boundaries of traditional jazz music.
